{{Infobox company | name = Ironclad Games | logo = | slogan = | type = [[Private company|Private]] | foundation = 2003 | location = [[Burnaby]], [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | revenue = | products = ''[[Sins of a Solar Empire]]'', ''[[Sins of a Dark Age]]'' }}
'''Ironclad Games''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[Personal computer game|PC game]] [[video game developer|developer]]. The company was founded in 2003 by former employees of [[Rockstar Vancouver]]. Ironclad is located in [[Burnaby]], [[British Columbia]].
==Titles== Ironclad released their first game, ''[[Sins of a Solar Empire]]'' on February 4, 2008, a game that features a mix of components from [[real-time strategy]] and [[4x game|4X]] strategy games. They released the ''Entrenchment'' expansion on February 11, 2009. The second expansion pack, ''Diplomacy'', was released on February 9, 2010. On February 21, 2012, they announced ''[[Sins of a Dark Age]]'', a [[multiplayer online battle arena]] game set in a pre-war fantasy environment. A standalone expansion pack called ''Rebellion'', was also released for ''Sins of a Solar Empire'' on June 12, 2012.
==Iron engine== Ironclad's Iron Engine supports a number of advanced features including per-pixel [[specular lighting]], [[dynamic fractal generation]], [[Video post-processing|post-process]] [[Bloom (shader effect)|bloom]] filtering, [[environment mapping]], custom pixel and vertex shaders for all [[Polygon mesh|meshes]] and effects and an advanced particle system.
v1.0 was used in ''[[Sins of a Solar Empire]]'' (2008).
v2.0 was used in ''[[Sins of a Dark Age]]'' (2012).
