{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}} {{Use British English|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox company |name = Oxford Friend |logo = |type = |founded = 1980 |alt = |location_city = |location_country = [[Oxford]], [[Oxfordshire]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom]] |locations = |homepage = [http://oxfordfriend.co.uk OxfordFriend.co.uk] }}
{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} {{Use British English|date=May 2015}} '''Oxford Friend''' is an [[Oxford]]<nowiki/>shire-based [[LGBT]]Q+ charity providing emotional support and counselling to the lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender community. The original volunteers were part of the local branch of the [[Campaign for Homosexual Equality]] (CHE). Listening services are provided by telephone, email, Facebook and instant messaging.<ref name=oxfriend1>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxfordfriend.co.uk/services.html|title=Services provided by Oxford Friend|publisher=Oxford Friend|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref> The charity also provides training on LGBTQ+ issues for educational institutions and other organisations in and around Oxfordshire. Oxford Friend raises money via a grant from [[Oxford City Council]] (as part of their campaign to support the LGBTQ+ community),<ref name=council>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxford.gov.uk/PageRender/decC/LGBTpeople|title=Equality, Diversity, and Inclusion - Lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender (LGBT) people|publisher=Oxford City Council|accessdate=2011-03-15}}</ref> donations, and external training packages.<ref name=oxfriend2>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxfordfriend.co.uk/about.html#finance|title=Oxford Friend's Finances|publisher=Oxford Friend|accessdate=2011-02-14}}</ref>
The group was established in 1980<ref name=oxfordtimes>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxfordtimes.co.uk/leisure/3964592.Friendly_advice_just_one_call_away/|title=Friendly advice just one call away|date=2008-12-10|publisher=The Oxford Times|accessdate=2011-03-15}}</ref> and registered as a charity in 1988. In 2006 the group was awarded the [[Queen's Award for Voluntary Service]].<ref name=queensaward2006>{{cite web|url=http://www.queensawardvoluntary.gov.uk/winners/southeast06.html|title=2006 winners of the Queen's Award for Voluntary Service in South-East England|publisher=The National Archives|accessdate=2011-03-15|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20090416141123/http://www.queensawardvoluntary.gov.uk/winners/southeast06.html|archivedate=16 April 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
