The '''Showmen's Guild of Great Britain''' exists to protect the interests of travelling [[showmen]] in [[Great Britain]].
The Showmen's Guild was founded as the '''United Kingdom Van Dwellers Protection Association''' in 1889 in [[Salford, Greater Manchester|Salford]].<ref>{{Citation | title = The Showmen's Guild of Great Britain: Notes on the Early History and Organisation of the Guild | work = ''All The Fun Of The Fair'' | url = http://www.fun-fairs.co.uk/guildhis.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080407221517/http://www.fun-fairs.co.uk/guildhis.html | archivedate = 7 April 2008}}</ref> In 1917, the Showmen's Guild of Great Britain, as it became known, was recognised as the [[trade association]] for the [[travelling funfair]] business.<ref>{{Citation | title = Showmen's guilds | work = '' National Fairground Archive'' | publisher = [[University of Sheffield]] | url = http://hri.shef.ac.uk/fairground/guilds.html | accessdate = 17 June 2010 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110717021100/http://hri.shef.ac.uk/fairground/guilds.html | archivedate = 17 July 2011 | df = }}</ref> It acquired the right to represent the business at local and national levels. It exists to promote and protect the Showmen's way of life and to preserve the unique cultural heritage of travelling fairs and circuses.
The Guild has a code of rules and also makes representations concerning proposed [[legislation]] when appropriate. It has a membership of around 4,700 people and is organized into ten regional sections. The current General Secretary, since April 2018, is Joe Mercer.<ref>{{Citation | title = The Role Of The Guild | work = ''All The Fun Of The Fair'' | url = http://www.fun-fairs.co.uk/guildrol.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080408160615/http://www.fun-fairs.co.uk/guildrol.html | archivedate = 8 April 2008}}</ref> It supports the National Fairground Archive, set up in 1994 at the [[University of Sheffield]].<ref>{{Citation | title = Home Page | work = ''National Fairground Archive'' | publisher = University of Sheffield | url = http://www.nfa.dept.shef.ac.uk/ | accessdate =17 June 2010}}</ref> The Showmen's Guild organizes fairs, such as [[St Giles' Fair]] in [[Oxford]], co-organized with the [[Oxford City Council]].<ref name="nfa-oxford">{{Citation | title = Oxford St Giles | work = ''National Fairground Archive'' | publisher = University of Sheffield | url = http://www.nfa.dept.shef.ac.uk/history/charter/oxford.html | accessdate = 17 June 2010 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090821143947/http://www.nfa.dept.shef.ac.uk/history/charter/oxford.html | archivedate = 21 August 2009 | df = }}</ref>
