{{Infobox comic book title <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> |title = The Bozz Chronicles |image = |imagesize = <!-- default 250 --> |caption = ''The Bozz Chronicles'' #1, cover art by [[Bret Blevins]] |schedule = |limited = |genre = Science fiction |publisher = [[Epic Comics]] (Marvel) |date = [[1985 in comics|1985]]–[[1986 in comics|1986]] |issues = |main_char_team = |writers = [[David Michelinie]] |artists = [[Bret Blevins]] |pencillers = |inkers = |letterers = |colorists = |editors = |creative_team_month = |creative_team_year = |creators = [[David Michelinie]] |subcat = Epic Comics |sort = Bozz Chroincles }}
'''''The Bozz Chronicles''''', now a [[graphic novel]], was originally a six-issue [[comic book]] series written by [[David Michelinie]], with artwork by Bret Blevins and John Ridgway.<ref>{{Cite book|title = The BOZZ Chronicles|publisher = Dover Publications|date = 2015-09-16|location = Place of publication not identified|isbn = 9780486798516|first = David|last = Michelinie|first2 = John|last2 = Ridgway|first3 = Brandon|last3 = Graham}}</ref> The original series was published by [[Epic Comics]] from December 1985 - December 1986.<ref>{{Cite web|title = The Bozz Chronicles (Volume) - Comic Vine|url = http://www.comicvine.com/the-bozz-chronicles/4050-3473/|website = www.comicvine.com|accessdate = 2015-09-02}}</ref> The series was set primarily in [[Victorian era]] England and centered on the crime-solving adventures of "Bozz", an [[Extraterrestrial life|alien]] with a long tail and an unpronounceable name who crash-landed on Earth. Bozz partners with prostitute [[Amanda Flynn (comics)|Amanda Flynn]] and American [[Salem Hawkshaw]] to solve crimes as a means of stimulating his mind and avoiding suicidal thoughts brought on by [[wiktionary:Ennui|ennui]]. Most mysteries presented in the series were [[paranormal]] or [[Speculative fiction|speculative]] in nature, for example, resurrection, death rays, and portals to hell.<ref>http://www.comicvine.com/bozz-chronicles-the/49-3473/ ''Bozz Chronices, The (Epic comics)'' - Comic Vine</ref> In 2014, it was announced that the six issue series would finally be collected into one publication by [[Dover Publications]] in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Lost no more... The Bozz Chronicles - Forbidden Planet Blog|url = http://www.forbiddenplanet.co.uk/blog/2014/lost-no-more-the-bozz-chronicles/|accessdate = 2015-09-02}}</ref>
